## Location of Henry County in Iowa  

This section serves as a comprehensive overview of the geographical positioning of Henry County within the state of Iowa, United States. The county’s boundaries, demographic statistics, and neighboring regions are described in detail, providing context for the subsequent historical listings.  

The county seat is **[Mount Pleasant](/Mount_Pleasant,_Iowa)**, a city that functions as the administrative and cultural hub of the area. Additional municipalities and communities within the county include **[Coppock](/Coppock,_Iowa)** (which also extends into neighboring jurisdictions), **[Hillsboro](/Hillsboro,_Iowa)**, **[New London](/New_London,_Iowa)**, **[Olds](/Olds,_Iowa)**, **[Rome](/Rome,_Iowa)**, **[Salem](/Salem,_Iowa)**, **[Wayland](/Wayland,_Iowa)**, **[Westwood](/Westwood,_Iowa)**, and **[Winfield](/Winfield,_Iowa)**.  

Census‑designated places (CDPs) located wholly or partially within the county comprise **[Lowell](/Lowell,_Iowa)**, **[Mount Union](/Mount_Union,_Iowa)**, **[Swedesburg](/Swedesburg,_Iowa)**, and **[Trenton](/Trenton,_Iowa)**. An unincorporated community, **[Oakland Mills](/Oakland_Mills,_Iowa)**, further diversifies the county’s settlement pattern.  

A map of Iowa highlighting Henry County is available for visual reference, and the county’s location can be contextualized within the broader Midwestern United States.  

